                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#99r">Fol. 99r</locus>: Supplication note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 99r: ምስለ፡ ፍቁራኒሁ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ወገብረ፡ ዋህድ፡ ጸሐፊ፡ አሜን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 99r: Fol. 99r: With his beloved priest Gäbrä Ḥǝywät and the scribe Gäbrä Wahǝd. Amen.</q>
                           By a secondary hand; incomplete (?)
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#100v">Fol. 100v</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 100v: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጅአዝማች፡ ምራጭ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለመቅደሰ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍሱ፡ ወስመ፡ ክርስትናሁ፡ ገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ወስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ገብረ፡ አምላክ፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወደቂቁ፡ ወለተ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወለተ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወለተ፡ አረጋዊ፡ እግዚእ፡ ኃረያ፡ ወለተ፡ ጻድቃን፡ ወለተ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ለይኩን ... </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 100v: This book is of däğğʾazmač Mǝrraḉ who donated it to the sanctuary of Ṗäraqliṭos so that it might be for him salvation of his soul. His baptismal name is Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer, the name of his father is Gäbrä ʾAmlak, and his mother is Wälättä ʾƎgziʾ, and his wife Wälättä Maryam, and his children Wälättä Täklä-Haymanot, Wälättä Haymanot, Wälättä ʾArägawi, ʾƎgziʾ Ḫaräya, Wälättä Ṣadǝqan, Wälättä ʾIyäsus. For ever and ever Amen. So be it …</q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ተ/ሚካኤል has been written on the front cover in yellow paint.&#xD;
- Crude notes and doodles on fols. 1r, 92av, 101r&#xD;
- Illegible ownership note on fol. 2r.&#xD;
- Names written over erased names: Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (e.g., fols. 18ra, 27rb, 93ra), Wälättä Maryam (e.g., fols. 27ra, 29ra, 35ra), Wälättä ʾƎgziʾ (fol. 39va,), Wälätä Täklä Haymanot (fols. 48ra, 97ra) Wälätl Haymanot (fol. 78rb).&#xD;
- Immediate correction indicated by series of dashes and thin lines above and below the word (fol. 63r).&#xD;
- A word corrected interlineally on fol. 83ra.&#xD;
- Crudely written sälam-hymn to Archangel Michael and other notes on fol. 101v.</item>
